P(A)=\frac{4}{5}
P(B)=\frac{1}{4}
\frac{1}{20}\le P(A \cap B)\le\frac{1}{4}
P(A \cap B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cup B)
A\cap B\subset B
P(A\cap B)\leq P(B) =\frac14
P(A\cap B) = P(A)+P(B)-P(A\cup B)\geq \frac45+\frac14-1=\frac1{20}
1 \ge P(A \cup B)  =  P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B)
 P(A \cap B) \ge P(A) + P(B) - 1
